## Handoff Protocols

<!-- WHY: Defines the exact format agents use to pass work to each other. -->
<!-- WHY: Without this, each handoff is ad-hoc and quality is unpredictable. -->

### Standard Handoff Format

When any agent hands off to another, it must include:

```markdown
## Handoff: [Source Agent] → [Target Agent]
**Task:** [What the target agent needs to do]
**Work Completed:** [What has been done already]
**Current State:** [File/data that exists now]
**Constraints:** [Time, format, requirements from user]
**Priority:** [High | Medium | Low]
```

